'''Kawashima Shrine''' (かわしまじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Kōnan|Q820496|qid=Q820496|1=Kōnan, Aichi}}, {{ill|lt=Aichi Prefecture|Q80434|qid=Q80434|1=Aichi Prefecture}}. It is one candidate shrine for "Kawashima Shrine" in Haguri District of {{ill|lt=Owari Province|Q514506|qid=Q514506|1=Owari Province}} in the '{{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}', though there are many differing theories.

=== History ===
Its founding time is unknown. Until the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Edo period|1=Edo period|qid=Q184963}}, it was called '''Gozu Tennō''', and is said to have declined due to repeated floods. The site was formerly called "Tenjinmori." In the mid-Edo period, a theory emerged identifying it as the Haguri District "Kawashima Shrine" in the Engishiki register, and it was rebuilt. In {{ill|lt=1898|Q7848|qid=Q7848|1=1898}} ({{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|qid=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} 31), it was officially renamed "Kawashima Shrine."

However, the Shikinaisha "Kawashima Shrine" has multiple candidate shrines and is not settled in scholarship. This is said to be because the nearby {{ill|lt=Kiso River|Q779607|qid=Q779607|1=Kiso River}} repeatedly flooded and washed away shrine buildings, making exact identification unclear. Candidate shrines include:

* Kawashima Shrine: Miyata-chō, Konan, Aichi
* {{ill|lt=Shirahige Shrine (Kasada-chō Kawashima, Kakamigahara)|Q124668655|qid=Q124668655|lt=Shirahige Shrine|1=Shirahige Shrine (Kakamigahara)}}: {{ill|lt=Kawashima Kasada-chō|Q131938355|qid=Q131938355|1=Kawashima Kasada-chō}}, {{ill|lt=Kakamigahara|Q641491|qid=Q641491|1=Kakamigahara}}, {{ill|lt=Gifu Prefecture|Q131277|qid=Q131277|1=Gifu Prefecture}}
* {{ill|lt=Enoki Shrine (Kakamigahara)|Q134893091|qid=Q134893091|lt=Enoki Shrine|1=Enoki Shrine}}: {{ill|lt=Kawashima Matsukura-chō|Q131870131|qid=Q131870131|1=Kawashima Matsukura-machi}}, Kakamigahara, Gifu
* Kawashima Tenjin Shrine (precinct shrine of {{ill|lt=Wakaguri Shrine|Q11616546|qid=Q11616546|1=Waguri Shrine}}): Shimamura, {{ill|lt=Ichinomiya|Q270810|qid=Q270810|1=Ichinomiya, Aichi}}, Aichi
* {{ill|lt=Uenoshima Shinmei Shrine|Q11358370|qid=Q11358370|1=Kaminoshima-Shinmei Shrine}}: Kawashima Matsukura-chō, Kakamigahara, Gifu
* {{ill|lt=Shamiya Shrine (Kakamigahara)|UNKNOWN|lt=Shamiya Shrine}}: {{ill|lt=Narukiyo-chō|Q131983825|qid=Q131983825|1=Narukiyo-chō}}, Kakamigahara, Gifu
* {{ill|lt=Shirahige Shrine (Matsumoto-chō, Kakamigahara)|Q134987078|qid=Q134987078|lt=Shirahige Shrine|1=Shirahige Shrine}}: {{ill|lt=Matsumoto-chō (Kakamigahara)|Q131870034|qid=Q131870034|lt=Matsumoto-chō|1=Matsumoto-chō}}, Kakamigahara, Gifu
* {{ill|lt=Yatsurugi Shrine (Ginan)|Q11390592|qid=Q11390592|lt=Yatsurugi Shrine|1=Yatsurugi Shrine (Ginan)}}: Miyamachi, {{ill|lt=Ginan|Q1204285|qid=Q1204285|1=Ginan, Gifu}}, {{ill|lt=Hashima District|Q615068|qid=Q615068|1=Hashima District, Gifu}}, Gifu

According to surviving passages of the '{{ill|lt=Owari no Kuni Fudoki|Q135598023|qid=Q135598023|1=Owari no Kuni Fudoki}}', the Shikinaisha "Kawashima Shrine" was in Kawashima Village, Kawanuma-gō, Haguri District, and was a shrine built by imperial order after a {{ill|lt=white deer|Q72616124|qid=Q72616124|1=white deer}} appeared from time to time in the reign of {{ill|lt=Emperor Shōmu|Q349263|qid=Q349263|1=Emperor Shōmu}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* Main deity
** {{ill|lt=Mizuhanome|Q8191796|qid=Q8191796|lt=Mizuhame-no-Kami|1=Mizuhanome}}
* Merged deities
** {{ill|lt=Susanoo|Q272993|qid=Q272993|lt=Susao-no-Mikoto|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto}}
** {{ill|qid=Q10936701|lt=Ōmononushi|Q10936701|qid=Q10936701|qid=Q10936701|lt=Ōmononushi-no-Kami|1=Ōmononushi}}
** {{ill|lt=Tokugawa Yoshinao|Q1136186|qid=Q1136186|1=Tokugawa Yoshinao}}
** {{ill|lt=Tokugawa Mitsutomo|Q843245|qid=Q843245|1=Tokugawa Mitsutomo}}
** {{ill|lt=Tokugawa Tsunashige|Q982743|qid=Q982743|1=Tokugawa Tsunanari}}

[[File:川島神社本殿.jpg|thumb|Honden of Kawashima Shrine]]

=== Transportation ===
* 15 minutes on foot from Meitetsu Bus "Hongōguchi" stop
** from {{ill|lt=Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station|Q2856589|qid=Q2856589|1=Meitetsu Ichinomiya Station}} on {{ill|lt=Nagoya Main Line|Q1137838|qid=Q1137838|lt=Meitetsu Nagoya Main Line|1=Meitetsu Nagoya Main Line}} / {{ill|lt=Bisai Line|Q901005|qid=Q901005|lt=Bisai Line|1=Meitetsu Bisai Line}}, and {{ill|lt=Owari-Ichinomiya Station|Q871495|qid=Q871495|1=Owari-Ichinomiya Station}} on the {{ill|lt=Tōkaidō Main Line|Q1190152|qid=Q1190152|1=Tōkaidō Main Line}} (Meitetsu Ichinomiya Bus Terminal stop 3), bound for "Miyata Hongō"
** from {{ill|lt=Kōnan Station (Aichi)|Q201473|qid=Q201473|lt=Kōnan Station|1=Kōnan Station (Aichi)}} on Meitetsu {{ill|lt=Inuyama Line|Q6810411|qid=Q6810411|lt=Inuyama Line|1=Meitetsu Inuyama Line}}, bound for "Kawashima"

